{
  "texts": [
    "The developed architecture is applied to the ADNI dataset and measured by several metrics such as precision, recall, accuracy, and F1-score.",
    "The proposed method recognized text with an accuracy of 93.2%, exceeding what was done by the transformer-based (90.1%) and CNN-based (90.8%) models.",
    "Self-supervised pre-training methods such as DINO typically necessitate substantial data volumes to achieve meaningful representation learning.",
    "This can be particularly challenging in medical imaging, where datasets are frequently constrained in size.Several studies have proposed innovative approaches for the early diagnosis of AD using deep learning techniques applied to medical imaging data, particularly MRI scans.",
    "Sethi et al. [79] introduced a CNN-SVM model that combines the feature extraction capabilities of CNN with the classification abilities of SVM."
  ]
}